Kenya's deputy environment minister, Maathai, spearheaded a successful campaign to reduce plastic bag usage by 90% in just a year.
The United Nations Environment Programme supported the ban on plastic bags, emphasizing the environmental and health risks they pose.
The government imposed fines on those involved in plastic bag production and distribution.
Similar initiatives have been seen globally, with varying degrees of success.
Rwanda and Uganda have also taken steps to combat plastic pollution, with Rwanda banning plastic bags entirely.
Tanzania is set to establish a recycling plant to address the growing plastic waste issue.
